11. Hierarchical Utilisation
----------------------------

+------------------------------+------+------+-------+------+------+
|           Instance           | LUTs | FFs  | BRAM36 | DSPs | IOs  |
+------------------------------+------+------+-------+------+------+
| neuraedge_top (top)          |  218 |  115 |     0  |    0 |   56 |
|   u_core (neuraedge)         | 1394 | 1633 |     1  |    0 |    0 |
|     u_enc (encoder)          |   38 |   12 |     0  |    0 |    0 |
|     u_smem (synapse_mem)     |    4 |    2 |     1  |    0 |    0 |
|     u_router (spike_router)  |  132 |  312 |     0  |    0 |    0 |
|     u_stdp (stdp)            |   88 |  560 |     0  |    0 |    0 |
|     u_sched (scheduler)      |   42 |   58 |     0  |    0 |    0 |
|     u_neu (neuron_array)     |  958 |  384 |     0  |    0 |    0 |
|       gen_neurons[0..31]     |   30 |   12 |     0  |    0 |    0 |
|     gen_sc[0..31]            |   92 |  256 |     0  |    0 |    0 |
|     gen_isyn[0..31]          |   40 |   49 |     0  |    0 |    0 |
+------------------------------+------+------+-------+------+------+

NOTE: Each LIF neuron instance (neuron.sv ×32) uses ~30 LUTs and 12 FFs.
      The 8-bit × 8-bit leak multiply is mapped to LUT6 chains (no DSP48 consumed).
      synapse_mem is inferred as a single RAMB36E1 (8 kb, 1 KB effective).
